in her situation

106
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:41,070
would be pretty depressed.

107
00:05:41,103 --> 00:05:42,303
Was it--

108
00:05:42,336 --> 00:05:44,103
-Suicide.

109
00:05:44,136 --> 00:05:45,036
-No.

110
00:05:45,070 --> 00:05:47,270
The Naomi Misora
I knew was strong.

111
00:05:47,303 --> 00:05:50,336
Not to mention, she was
also an excellent FBI agent.

112
00:05:50,370 --> 00:05:54,536
If anything, it's more likely
she'd be trying to catch Kira.

113
00:05:54,570 --> 00:05:57,203
It appears she came
to Japan with Penber.

114
00:05:57,236 --> 00:06:00,136
It's possible that she
may have found a lead.

115
00:06:00,170 --> 00:06:05,236
If that's the case, did Kira
manage to get her first?

116
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:07,870
Everyone, at this point I'd
like to focus our investigation

117
00:06:07,903 --> 00:06:11,003
on only those people who
Raye Penber was tailing.

118
00:06:11,036 --> 00:06:14,570
In particular, he was assigned
to two police officers

119
00:06:14,603 --> 00:06:16,370
and those closest to them.

120
00:06:16,403 --> 00:06:18,136
-Very well, who are
these two individuals

121
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:20,070
he was investigating?

122
00:06:20,103 --> 00:06:25,036
-Deputy Director Kitamura, along
with Detective Superintendent

123
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:27,736
Yagami and their families.

124
00:06:27,770 --> 00:06:30,936
At this stage, I'd like to
place wiretaps and surveillance

125
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:34,203
cameras in both households.

126
00:06:34,236 --> 00:06:36,836
-I have to make sure there's no
evidence left on this computer,

127
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:38,370
just in case someone
goes through it.

128
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:43,036
Now I just have to
hide these clippings

129
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:46,270
from the death note in here.

130
00:06:46,303 --> 00:06:49,336
RYUK: It seems like you're
pretty skilled with your hands.

131
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:51,870
I bet you're pretty popular
with the girls, aren't you?

132
00:06:51,903 --> 00:06:53,770
LIGHT: Skill has
nothing to do with it.

133
00:06:53,803 --> 00:06:55,970
It's your looks that count.

134
00:06:56,003 --> 00:06:58,636
I'm guessing you're not
that popular, are you?

135
00:06:58,670 --> 00:07:00,103
Huh?

136
00:07:00,136 --> 00:07:01,236
-Surveillance cameras?

137
00:07:01,748 --> 00:07:02,881
Ryuzaki.

138
00:07:02,914 --> 00:07:05,081
I don't see how you
could even consider this.

139
00:07:05,114 --> 00:07:06,781
If this got out, we'd
have a civil rights

140
00:07:06,814 --> 00:07:07,714
scandal on our hands.

141
00:07:07,748 --> 00:07:08,781
We'd all lose our jobs.

142
00:07:08,814 --> 00:07:10,481
-You told me you'd
be willing to risk

143
00:07:10,514 --> 00:07:11,981
your lives for
this investigation,

144
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:14,481
but you wouldn't risk your jobs?

145
00:07:14,514 --> 00:07:16,681
-Ryuzaki, what are
the odds that Kira's

146
00:07:16,714 --> 00:07:19,548
in one of those households?

147
00:07:19,581 --> 00:07:21,548
-Maybe 10%.

148
00:07:21,581 --> 00:07:23,714
No, it's closer to 5%.

149
00:07:23,748 --> 00:07:24,814
-Seriously?

150
00:07:24,848 --> 00:07:26,448
I'm sorry, but it's
not worth the risk.

151
00:07:26,481 --> 00:07:26,998
SOICHIRO YAGAMI: No.

152
00:07:27,031 --> 00:07:29,064
Of all the people we've
investigated so far,

153
00:07:29,098 --> 00:07:32,198
not one of them seemed even
the least bit suspicious.

154
00:07:32,231 --> 00:07:33,998
Even if there's
only a 1% chance,

155
00:07:34,031 --> 00:07:35,664
we simply can't
afford to ignore it.

156
00:07:35,698 --> 00:07:37,031
SHUICHI AIZAWA: Chief?

157
00:07:37,064 --> 00:07:38,631
-I don't have to
tell you how offended

158
00:07:38,664 --> 00:07:41,398
I am to learn my family
is under suspicion.

159
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:44,869
Having said that,
just go ahead with it.

160
00:07:44,902 --> 00:07:46,702
And make sure you
install them everywhere.

161
00:07:46,736 --> 00:07:48,469
I don't want any blind
spots in the house,

162
00:07:48,502 --> 00:07:50,736
and that includes the bathroom.

163
00:07:50,769 --> 00:07:52,269
-Thank you very much.

164
00:07:52,302 --> 00:07:53,402
That was my intention.

165
00:07:53,436 --> 00:07:54,169
-Come on, Chief.

166
00:07:54,202 --> 00:07:55,569
You don't have to agree to this.

167
00:07:55,602 --> 00:07:56,769
-Yes, he's right!

168
00:07:56,802 --> 00:07:57,969
Think about your family.

169
00:07:58,002 --> 00:08:00,069
You have a wife and
daughter at home, don't you?

170
00:08:00,102 --> 00:08:01,969
-Yes, I'm well
aware of that fact.

171
00:08:02,002 --> 00:08:04,294
But there is no point
in doing any of this

172
00:08:04,328 --> 00:08:05,361
if we can't be thorough.

173
00:08:05,394 --> 00:08:07,161
Now I suggest you keep quiet!

174
00:08:10,894 --> 00:08:11,894
-I'm sorry.

175
00:08:11,928 --> 00:08:14,294
-No, it's OK.

176
00:08:14,328 --> 00:08:17,528
Excuse me.

177
00:08:17,561 --> 00:08:19,961
-As a courtesy to the
chief and his family,

178
00:08:19,994 --> 00:08:23,728
only he and I will conduct
surveillance of their home.

179
00:08:23,761 --> 00:08:25,861
Watari, how long will
it take to prepare

180
00:08:25,894 --> 00:08:28,694
the wiretaps and
cameras we need?

181
00:08:28,728 --> 00:08:31,794
-Well, starting tomorrow I
can set them up at any time

182
00:08:31,828 --> 00:08:34,128
provided we know when
both houses will be empty.

183
00:08:37,628 --> 00:08:39,161
-See you later, Light.

184
00:08:39,194 --> 00:08:40,228
-Yeah, see you tomorrow.

185
00:08:43,894 --> 00:08:45,194
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): What?

186
00:08:45,228 --> 00:08:45,928
No one's home yet.

187
00:08:55,194 --> 00:08:55,994
I'm home.

188
00:09:05,961 --> 00:09:07,928
Huh?

189
00:09:07,961 --> 00:09:08,428
Hmm.

190
00:09:12,294 --> 00:09:13,528
RYUK: How's it going?

191
00:09:13,561 --> 00:09:15,694
I don't think anyone else
is in the house right no.

192
00:09:15,728 --> 00:09:19,628
Do you want to play
some video games?

193
00:09:19,661 --> 00:09:22,528
Come on, it's been a while.

194
00:09:22,561 --> 00:09:23,128
You listening?

195
00:09:28,361 --> 00:09:29,094
Hey, Light.

196
00:09:36,028 --> 00:09:37,661
-I don't believe it.

197
00:09:37,694 --> 00:09:39,761
I never knew he went
to such great lengths.

198
00:09:39,794 --> 00:09:41,528
What could he be
hiding in there that he

199
00:09:41,561 --> 00:09:43,461
doesn't want anyone else to see?

200
00:09:43,494 --> 00:09:45,161
-For a 17-year-old
kid, I wouldn't

201
00:09:45,194 --> 00:09:48,594
say this kind of behavior
is particularly abnormal.

202
00:09:48,628 --> 00:09:51,128
When I was his age, I
did strange things, too.

203
00:09:51,161 --> 00:09:53,661
Have you ever talked to your
son about the investigation?

204
00:09:53,694 --> 00:09:54,794
-Of course not.

205
00:09:54,828 --> 00:09:56,694
I've never once revealed
classified information

206
00:09:56,728 --> 00:09:57,994
to my family.

207
00:09:58,028 --> 00:10:01,028
Besides, I don't get to see
them too often these days.

208
00:10:01,061 --> 00:10:04,528
And usually as soon as I get
home, all I can do is sleep.

209
00:10:04,561 --> 00:10:06,728
-I understand.

210
00:10:06,761 --> 00:10:08,228
-Where exactly are we going?

211
00:10:10,961 --> 00:10:15,361
Light, don't ignore me when I'm
talking to you or I'll get mad.

212
00:10:15,394 --> 00:10:16,294
Huh?

213
00:10:16,328 --> 00:10:17,728
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
It doesn't look

214
00:10:17,761 --> 00:10:19,228
like these clothes
have been bugged.

215
00:10:19,261 --> 00:10:20,261
RYUK: Hello?

216
00:10:20,294 --> 00:10:20,735
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
I think we're safe.

217
00:10:20,769 --> 00:10:21,769
-Yoohoo.

218
00:10:21,802 --> 00:10:22,735
-Listen to me.

219
00:10:22,769 --> 00:10:24,469
There's a very
strong possibility

220
00:10:24,502 --> 00:10:26,069
that there are
wiretaps and maybe

221
00:10:26,102 --> 00:10:28,902
surveillance cameras
hidden throughout my house.

222
00:10:28,935 --> 00:10:30,269
-Really?

223
00:10:30,302 --> 00:10:32,735
But that piece of paper was
still in your door, wasn't it?

224
00:10:32,769 --> 00:10:35,769
-That's true, but I left the
paper in the door in a way

225
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:38,035
that it would be obvious to
anyone entering the room.

226
00:10:38,069 --> 00:10:39,802
The real test is the handle.

227
00:10:39,835 --> 00:10:40,902
-It is?

228
00:10:40,935 --> 00:10:42,402
-When that door is
closed, the door

229
00:10:42,435 --> 00:10:44,869
handle automatically returns
to a horizontal position,

230
00:10:44,902 --> 00:10:46,635
and it won't go any
higher than that.

231
00:10:46,669 --> 00:10:49,602
But whenever I close the
door, I adjust it slightly.

232
00:10:49,635 --> 00:10:51,235
Instead of letting
it sit horizontally,

233
00:10:51,269 --> 00:10:53,702
I lower it by about
five millimeters.

234
00:10:53,735 --> 00:10:55,802
When I get home and I
try to open the door,

235
00:10:55,835 --> 00:10:57,302
if the handle is
all the way up, I

236
00:10:57,335 --> 00:11:00,535
can be fairly certain that
someone was in my room.

237
00:11:00,569 --> 00:11:02,069
But that method
alone doesn't tell me

238
00:11:02,102 --> 00:11:04,069
if my door was actually opened.

239
00:11:04,102 --> 00:11:07,235
So I put a mechanical pencil
lead in place, as well.

240
00:11:07,269 --> 00:11:09,002
-So what you do with it?

241
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,735
-It goes on the hinge.

242
00:11:10,769 --> 00:11:13,202
After I close the door, I take
the pencil lead and rest it

243
00:11:13,235 --> 00:11:14,602
on the hinge in
such a way that it

244
00:11:14,635 --> 00:11:17,335
will break if the door happens
to be opened by anyone.

245
00:11:17,369 --> 00:11:20,502
Normally, I take it out
myself when I get back home.

246
00:11:20,535 --> 00:11:22,035
When I got home
from school today,

247
00:11:22,069 --> 00:11:24,269
I noticed that the
pencil lead was broken.

248
00:11:24,302 --> 00:11:26,969
-Now that you mention
it, I do remember that.

249
00:11:27,002 --> 00:11:29,302
-First the door
handle, then the lead.

250
00:11:29,335 --> 00:11:31,535
I know someone was
in there today.

251
00:11:31,569 --> 00:11:33,102
-Maybe it was your mother.

252
00:11:33,135 --> 00:11:35,669
-My family wouldn't have
noticed the piece of paper.

253
00:11:35,702 --> 00:11:37,735
What's suspicious is that
